31/10/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Three Bosnian Serb parties -- the Union of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), the Democratic People's Alliance and the Socialist Party of Republika Srpska (RS) -- have agreed to form the next coalition government in RS. Entity Prime Minister Milorad Dodik, leader of the SNSD, announced the news Monday (October 30th), but said the door to other parties remains open. The three parties control 48 of the 83 seats in parliament, following the October 1st elections.
In other news, BiH's chief negotiator with the EU, Igor Davidovic, and the head of the BiH government's directorate for European integration, Osman Topcagic, are visiting Washington. They are briefing officials on developments in BiH's European integration process. (Dnevni avaz - 31/10/06; RTRS, Srna - 30/10/06)
